## Steps to Reproduce

1) Try to create a new flutter project through File -> New Project. After completing the wizard you get an error that 'at least one platform must be selected' even though all fields were filled in.

2) Flutter inspector just fails with the following output for me:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5325112/106369979-e8079080-6377-11eb-86c7-d8a99543ed38.png)

comment_data.body:
I'm also seeing this problem with the 1.22.5 SDK, so the issue when creating a new project was presumably caused by the Flutter plug-in, which was just updated.
I'm seeing it with plugin version 53.0.2.
Same issue here, Flutter plugin version 53.0.5 using Intellij Idea.
FYI you can manually revert back by downloading the previous version and installing the zip.
Thanks for the reports! This was actually caused by https://github.com/flutter/devtools/issues/2653, which is now resolved.

I just did a brand new install on windows
Flutter 1.22.6
Android SDK 30.0.3
IntelliJ 2020.1.4
And I am still getting the platform error.

I had the same issue. Manually installing this version fixed it for me.
https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9212-flutter/versions/stable/107560

Guess I'll wait a bit before updating :)

> I had the same issue. Manually installing this version fixed it for me.
> https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9212-flutter/versions/stable/107560
> 
> Guess I'll wait a bit before updating :)

This fixed it. But means there is still an issue in 53.0.2.
So, should I update or not?

> I had the same issue. Manually installing this version fixed it for me.
> https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9212-flutter/versions/stable/107560
> 
> Guess I'll wait a bit before updating :)

After manually installing version 52.2.5 I get the error "Incompatible (since build 203.5981.155 > IU-201.8743.12)" and I no longer have the option to create a Flutter project in the menu.
Do I need to install another version of Flutter as well, and not only the plugin?
Having similar issue on macOS. The "Platform" selection is not showing up when creating a new project.

Is this IntelliJ issue? As same as @Celesica, I can't create a new project anymore after updating my IntelliJ to 2021.3.2

```bash
[!] IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate Edition (version 2020.3.2)
    • IntelliJ at /Users/kakao/Applications/JetBrains Toolbox/IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate.app
    ✗ Flutter plugin not installed; this adds Flutter specific functionality.
    ✗ Dart plugin not installed; this adds Dart specific functionality.
    • For information about installing plugins, see
      https://flutter.dev/intellij-setup/#installing-the-plugins
```

but I installed both of them, respectively 53.0.5 / 203.6912. 

**Currently I manually create new project by `flutter create new_project` and it seems working** but I think we should reopen this issue.

@roeniss - can you open a new issue? This one was about a problem starting DevTools. We'd want to know the version of IntelliJ or Android Studio you're using, the version of the Flutter IntelliJ plugin, and the version of Flutter that you're on; thanks!
Hi, I had the same problem on Intellij IDEA. I just reinstalled the flutter plugin and solve the problem, may be that works for you also.
Thank you @echaelse! as devoncarew said, new patch was released so this issue is fixed now :)
How can I update the plugin manually?
@marvinvargasmachuca intellij -> preferences -> plugins tab -> flutter (installed tab) -> update -> restart IDE

title: Yesterday's update broke this plugin in multiple ways
